        <abstract>
            <p>Julius von Sachs’s views on stomata seem largely correct, but CD cannot understand how leaves can survive submerged for such long periods.</p> 
<p>Has been observing <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi> and concludes that none of the movement of the tentacles is caused by growth.</p> 
            <p>Suggests observations to show role of pulvinus in leaf movement.</p>
        </abstract>
